latestPosts.caption:
~ Bodrum’s Most Beautiful Surprise Wasn’t the View🐾🤍

When we were in Bodrum, staying at a hotel with cats roaming around the premises, one cat in particular found her way to us. She hung out with us at night and left—but the next morning, around 8 or 9, we heard persistent meowing outside our room. We opened the door, and there she was again. We let her in, and she climbed onto our bed. Moments later, to our complete surprise, she started giving birth—right there.

We quickly called the hotel staff, who were so kind and responsive. They brought towels and a box, and together we set up a warm, safe space for her in one of the quiet hotel lobbies. While we had breakfast, she gave birth to seven beautiful, healthy kittens! 

Afterwards, we went back to check on her. She let us feed her, pet her, and gently shift her and the babies into fresh towels. She meowed at us—not with fear, but with trust. She chose us. Trusted us. And let us be part of one of the most intimate moments of her life!🥺
#mamma
